text.section:
The governing body of Anne Arundel County and of a municipal corporation in Anne Arundel County shall grant a property tax credit under this section against the county and municipal corporation property tax imposed on:
property that is:
owned by the United States Naval Academy Alumni Association, Incorporated;
located at the corner of College Avenue and King George Street in Annapolis, Maryland; and
known as Ogle Hall;
property that is:
owned by the Naval Academy Athletic Association; and
used for athletic events and purposes;
real property that is owned by the Three Rivers Sportsmen, Incorporated; and
property that is owned by the Maryland Ornithological Society, Incorporated.
